---
import TextPageLayout from "~/layouts/TextPageLayout.astro";

const lang = "en" as const;
---

<TextPageLayout
  lang={lang}
  title="Privacy policy"
  pathname="/en/privacy/"
  altLang="fr"
  altLangPath="/confidentialite/"
>
  <p>
    This policy describes how Anthony Profit processes personal data collected via the website
    <strong>anthonyprofit.com</strong>, in compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation
    (GDPR — EU Regulation 2016/679) and the French Data Protection Act.
  </p>

  <h2>Data controller</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Anthony Profit</strong> — Sole proprietor<br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:hello@anthonyprofit.com">hello@anthonyprofit.com</a>
  </p>

  <h2>Data collected</h2>
  <p>
    This site is static and uses <strong>no forms</strong>, no analytics tools, no advertising, and
    no tracking cookies. No personal data is automatically collected during your browsing.
  </p>
  <p>
    The only data that may be collected is what you voluntarily transmit by sending an email to
    <a href="mailto:hello@anthonyprofit.com">hello@anthonyprofit.com</a>: your email address,
    your name, and the content of your message.
  </p>

  <h2>Purpose of processing</h2>
  <p>Data received by email is used solely to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Respond to your quote request or inquiry;</li>
    <li>Establish a commercial relationship in the context of a service;</li>
    <li>Maintain a contractual record of exchanges (legal obligation).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Legal basis</h2>
  <p>
    Processing is based on your <strong>consent</strong> (voluntary email submission) and on the
    <strong>performance of pre-contractual measures</strong> taken at your request (Article 6.1.b
    of the GDPR).
  </p>

  <h2>Retention period</h2>
  <p>
    Emails are retained for the duration necessary for the commercial relationship, then archived
    for a maximum of 3 years from the last contact for commercial prospecting purposes, or longer
    if a legal obligation requires it (invoices: 10 years).
  </p>

  <h2>Recipients</h2>
  <p>Your data is processed by Anthony Profit and hosted by the following service providers:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Email inbox</strong>: email hosting provider (to specify actual provider)</li>
    <li><strong>Website hosting</strong>: Vercel Inc. (United States) — transfers covered by the
      European Commission's Standard Contractual Clauses</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    No data is sold, transferred to third parties for commercial purposes, or used for profiling.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>Under the GDPR, you have the following rights:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Right of access</strong> to your data;</li>
    <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong>;</li>
    <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> ("right to be forgotten");</li>
    <li><strong>Right to restriction</strong> of processing;</li>
    <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong>;</li>
    <li><strong>Right to object</strong> to processing;</li>
    <li><strong>Right to withdraw consent</strong> at any time;</li>
    <li><strong>Right to lodge a complaint</strong> with the French data protection authority
      CNIL (<a href="https://www.cnil.fr/en" rel="noopener" target="_blank">cnil.fr</a>).</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To exercise these rights, contact:
    <a href="mailto:hello@anthonyprofit.com">hello@anthonyprofit.com</a>. A response will be
    provided within a maximum of 30 days.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>This site does not use any cookies.</strong> No trackers are placed on your browser,
    for technical purposes (other than strictly necessary for operation), analytics, or
    advertising.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    The site is served over HTTPS (TLS 1.3) with HSTS enforced. Emails received are stored on a
    secure server. Anthony Profit implements appropriate technical and organisational measures to
    protect your data against unauthorised access, modification, disclosure or destruction.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    This policy may be updated to reflect changes in practices or legal obligations. The date of
    last modification appears below.
  </p>

  <p class="meta">Last updated: June 2026</p>
</TextPageLayout>
